<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FAN DRIVE CLUTCH: KYSOR 1090 (8000 SERIES) - MAINTENANCE - SYSTEM CHECKS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SYSTEM CHECKS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>To ensure proper safe operation of the fan clutch, perform the following checks prior to placing the
                vehicle back in service.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fan</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for cracked or missing fan blades, and loose fasteners. Replace defective fans.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque fan blade fasteners to values as specified in the
                    <hotlnk document="s12001j_HL1200101.xml" xrefid="hl1200101">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fan Belts</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Belt adjustment and alignment are necessary to ensure satisfactory component life.
                        Over-tightening belts will shorten hub bearing life. Loose belts will cause excessive belt wear.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check belt condition; replace if worn or frayed.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for proper tension.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for proper alignment.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Clutch</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the engine OFF, check for proper fan clutch engagement and disengagement by
                    applying 90-120 psi of clean air.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten clutch mounting bolts. Refer to the proper engine section in the service
                    manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the engine OFF and an external clean air source of 90-120 psi connected to the
                    clutch, the fan hub should turn freely by hand.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Check Shutter Operation and Cooling System</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Shutter should be open with key off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Shutters must open completely before the fan engages.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Ensure fan engages at correct temperature.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
